UnderworldPostcard376.name: Charwood [376]
description: Charwood is the last known vegetation in the Underworld. Popular
Cryptie camping hotspot and voted in the top 50 places you would
like to have your soul tortured for eternity. The floor basks in
a rooted warming evil glow, aeons of suffering and summer
holidays for many many unhappy Cryptie families.

UnderworldPostcard377.name: Earthly Gateway [377]
description: The Earthly Gateway is a structure that has been around since
the very beginning of the Underworld. It mostly lays dormant but
once or twice a year becomes active; allowing Crypties to enter
the Earthly realm. During this time the very ground on which the
structure stands begins to dematerialize amongst the raw energy
being transferred interdimensionally. Don't stand too close,
you may lose your favourite hat.

UnderworldPostcard378.name: Winding Watchtower [378]
description: The Winding Watchtower sits upon a vantage point to overlook the
maddening maze below in which unlucky Crypties who disobey the
laws of the Underworld are placed. It’s rumoured that the
quickest any Cryptie has escaped from the bewildering maze is 17
days and there have even been rumours of Crypties giving up once
inside and settling down in underground caverns created by the
lost and stranded.
